						<summary>

						<p>Stone set up near the <hi rend="italic">laṁbaḍi</hi> colony on the way to Palukūru.</p>						

						<p>1849 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It is dated in Śaka 1770, Saumya, Vaiśākha, śu. 6, corresponding to April 28, Saturday, 1848 A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records the settlement of the boundary dispute between the village Palukūru and Kanamala-cheṟuvu by Mēstaru Chenasu-dora and Hassamkhān-sāheb, the Tahsildāru of Vinikonḍa Talukā and setting up of the boundary stone on the west bank of the Sōmulavāgu with consent of the involved parties.</p>						

						</summary>
